        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "after htmlspecialchars() a word like \"R\u00e9tablir\" containing accentuated caracter output like this \"R\ufffdtablir\"\nhtmlentities() works in the same way as htmlspecialchars() but works on more caracters\nwhen I use  htmlentities() \"R\u00e9tablir\" output correctly as \"R\u00e9tablir\"\n\nmy source file are UTF8 encoded\nmy apache send HTML in UTF8\n\nif there is no special reason to use htmlspecialchars().\nI propose to replace all the call made to htmlspecialchars() in view and helper  with htmlentities().\nThis will permit the generalisation of the $this->escape() practise in view, including for people using accentuated caracters and the security will be better for every user of the Zend framework\n\nThe 0.1.3 version was also affected"
        },
