        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10308",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dime",
                        "name": "dime",
                        "displayName": "Didier Meulemans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "sample using the FormReset Helper with the text R\u00e9tablir.\nThe other accentuated caracters viewable on this screen are treated with  htmlentities()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dime",
                        "name": "dime",
                        "displayName": "Didier Meulemans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-06T08:40:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-06T08:40:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10651",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=felix",
                        "name": "felix",
                        "displayName": "Gunar Scholz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't think that this is an error of htmlspecialchars(). It seems your script is not properly utf-8 encoded.\n\nTry these examples\n{code}\nheader('Content-type: text\/html; charset=utf-8');\necho htmlspecialchars(\"utf-8 encoded: t\\xC3\\xA9st\") . '<br>';  \/\/ utf-8 encoded t\u00e9st\necho htmlspecialchars(\"iso-8859-1 encoded: t\\xE9st\"); \/\/ iso-8859-1 encoded t\u00e9st\n{code}\n\nResult is:\nutf8 encoded: t\u00e9st \niso-8859-1 encoded: t[questionmarksign]st\n\n{code}\nheader('Content-type: text\/html; charset=iso-8859-1');\necho htmlspecialchars(\"utf-8 encoded: t\\xC3\\xA9st\") . '<br>';  \/\/ utf-8 encoded t\u00e9st\necho htmlspecialchars(\"iso-8859-1 encoded: t\\xE9st\"); \/\/ iso-8859-1 encoded t\u00e9st\n{code}\n\nResult is:\nutf8 encoded: t\u00c3\u00a9st\niso-8859-1 encoded: t\u00e9st",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=felix",
                        "name": "felix",
                        "displayName": "Gunar Scholz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-02T05:28:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-02T05:28:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10774",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please see ZF-341 for an example solution and recommendations.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-05T20:07:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-05T20:07:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11105",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Revision 1429 addresses this issue by enforcing UTF-8 encoding when using htmlspecialchars or htmlentities throughout the Zend_View codebase.\n\nPlease check out latest svn and advise if this corrects the issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-02T00:27:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-02T00:27:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11280",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Due to the nature of the security announcement sent out by Stefan Esser earlier this week ([http:\/\/www.hardened-php.net\/advisory_132006.138.html]), I'm going to modify how this works:\n\n* By default, encode to ISO-8859-1 (latin1)\n* Add a setEncoding() accessor to allow setting encoding for escaping actions",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-10T13:48:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-10T13:48:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11389",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing fix version to 0.6.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-13T15:17:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-13T15:17:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11680",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Final changes added in revision 1902. Default encoding is ISO-8859-1 (latin1). set\/getEncoding() accessors added so this setting may be changed by the developer:\n{code}\n$view = new Zend_View();\n$view->setEncoding('UTF-8');\n{code}\nescape() will then use the encoding specified when filtering through htmlspecialchars() or htmlentities().",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-28T14:35:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-28T14:35:57.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
